<file path="README.md">
# Smart HR

AI-powered Human Resource Management platform (modular monolith: FastAPI + PostgreSQL + Next.js 15).

## Repository layout

```text
├── frontend/          # Next.js 15 (App Router) application
├── backend/           # FastAPI application
├── infrastructure/    # Docker, nginx, deployment scripts
├── docs/              # PRD, architecture, API spec, schema, implementation plan
├── docker-compose.yml # Local development services
└── .env.example       # Environment variable template (added in T-006)
```

See [docs/architecture.md](docs/architecture.md) for the full folder structure and design decisions.

## Prerequisites

- [Docker](https://docs.docker.com/get-docker/) and Docker Compose (recommended for local database)
- [Python](https://www.python.org/downloads/) 3.11+
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) 20 LTS+ (for frontend, added in T-012)

## Quick start (after scaffolding tasks)

These steps apply once backend (T-002–T-011) and frontend (T-012) tasks are complete.

### 1. Clone and configure environment

```bash
cp .env.example .env
# Edit .env with your local values (never commit .env)
```

### 2. Start infrastructure

```bash
docker compose up -d db
```

### 3. Backend

```bash
cd backend
python -m venv .venv
# Windows: .venv\Scripts\activate
# macOS/Linux: source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
alembic upgrade head
python scripts/seed.py
```

From the **monorepo root** (`AI_in_HRM/`):

```bash
python -m uvicorn backend.app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

Or from `backend/`:

```bash
uvicorn app.main:app --reload --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000
```

### Seed data (T-011)

The seed script is idempotent — safe to run multiple times:

```bash
cd backend
python scripts/seed.py
```

Bootstrap administrator:

| Field | Value |
